         <abstract id="aspace_948205bdaa3671f8c132717f846eca5d">Countee Cullen gained fame principally as a poet, during the Harlem Renaissance, and later taught in the New York City school system.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n50019600" source="naf">
